.TH "generic_access_phys" 9 "generic_access_phys" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
generic_access_phys \- generic implementation for iomem mmap access
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" generic_access_phys
.BI "(struct vm_area_struct *vma "  ","
.BI "unsigned long addr "  ","
.BI "void *buf "  ","
.BI "int len "  ","
.BI "int write "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "vma" 12
the vma to access
.IP "addr" 12
userspace addres, not relative offset within \fIvma\fP
.IP "buf" 12
buffer to read/write
.IP "len" 12
length of transfer
.IP "write" 12
set to FOLL_WRITE when writing, otherwise reading
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This is a generic implementation for \fIvm_operations_struct.access\fP for an
iomem mapping. This callback is used by \fBaccess_process_vm\fP when the \fIvma\fP is
not page based.
